Juan Yun: No-no-no! That's not...! Hold on... just let me breathe... for a second...
Juan Yun: Whew... It's not what you think.
Juan Yun: Something's going on at the hall. I was stopped by Maeok and asked for my opinion.
Tindoiimu: ...That's it?
Juan Yun: Yes. I'm sorry for being late, but please believe me. I wouldn't joke with my life on the line.

Juan Yun: That... might be difficult.
Tindoiimu: Are you sure this road is safe?
Juan Yun: Lake Lumina is Jellyfish Tribe territory. There's usually no one here on the weekdays.
Juan Yun: There are some monsters, but still one of the best ways to slip out of the Alliance unnoticed.
Tindoiimu: How do you know that? This being jellyfish territory and all.
Juan Yun: ...Because, I've been here.
Juan Yun: I served as hostage here with my mother, once.
Tingko: Lord Juan Yun, you were a hostage, too!?
Juan Yun: The East Alliance is a criss-cross of different tribes and cultures. Political hostages are more common than you might think.
Juan Yun: Don't look so surprised~
Jihasaha: ...But, you're the qilin lord...
Juan Yun: And so I'm even more valuable as a hostage.
Tindoiimu: ...Did Qing Feng... I mean, did your father make that decision?
Juan Yun: Him... To me, he is my father.

Juan Yun: To my mother, he is a husband... 
But to him, we're just pawns.
Juan Yun: Valuable pawns, but pawns nonetheless.
Juan Yun: Anyway, that's why I know about this path. Being able to use it now... I guess I didn't lose my legs for nothing.
Tindoiimu: ...You mean, your legs... you...
Juan Yun: When I was young and stupid, I tried to escape back home through this lake. A jellyfish latched onto my legs, and it lost all feeling...
Juan Yun: My life was spared, but they couldn't save my legs.
Tindoiimu: ...Don't laugh.
Juan Yun: I wanted to go home so badly, but... when they finally let me leave, I cried.
Juan Yun: I realized the part of me that could run and that could jump... would always be at the bottom of this damned lake.
Tindoiimu: Lord Juan Yun...
Juan Yun: ...And then I realized, home... it doesn't matter if you love it or hate it.
Juan Yun: If you spend time somewhere, and leave a piece of yourself there... that's home enough.
Tindoiimu: Stop laughing!
Juan Yun: ......
Tindoiimu: ...I get it, so stop laughing...
Tindoiimu: ...Please.
Juan Yun: ...Thank you, Princess.
